            ">China strong retaliation</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/us-president-trump-xi-jinping-china-state-visit.png" alt="US President Donald Trump walks with Xi Jinping, China's president" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>US President Donald Trump walks with Xi Jinping, China's president. Credits: Qilai Shen/Bloomberg
            </i></p>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">China’s Finance Ministry announced a revised <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-04-2025-h1-1-125-retaliatory-tariff" target="_blank">125% retaliatory tariff</a> on US goods, set to take effect on Saturday. The move comes as a response to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-04-2025-h1-2-trump-raising-tariffs" target="_blank">Trump raising tariffs</a> on Chinese imports to 145%, including a 20% “fentanyl tax,” aimed at punishing China for its alleged role in the production and export of precursor chemicals used in making fentanyl.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Beijing slammed the US tariff as economically senseless and filed a complaint with the World Trade Organization (WTO). They called their response “small and symbolic,” saying the tariff hike was triggered by the US escalation, not by choice. </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Asian markets dropped further on Friday, with Japan’s Nikkei 225 index down around 5% and most markets opening in the red. Meanwhile, Richard Painter, a former White House ethics lawyer, has called for an investigation into whether anyone knew of Trump's plans and benefited from them. He warned Trump to “avoid an economic crisis and an all-out trade war.”</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
