        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="             
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Clothing suppliers brace for tariff damage
        </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/vietnam-hit-by-trump-tariffs.png" alt="Vietnam was among the countries hardest hit by Trump's latest tariffs blitz" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Vietnam was among the countries hardest hit by Trump's latest tariffs blitz. Credits: Huu Kha/AFP</i></p>
        </mj-text>
      
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">The global clothing industry has become one of the biggest unexpected casualties of President Trump's latest tariff policy. As of 2025, 97% of the garments purchased in the US are made overseas, mostly in Asia. Those trade barriers are putting the future of US garment imports at risk.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Mark Anner, dean at Rutgers’ School of Management and Labor Relations, said the tariffs are unlikely to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-04-2025-h2-3-bring-textile-production-back" target="_blank">bring textile production back</a> to the US. The industry faces massive obstacles, including:</p>
          <ol style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom:5px; margin-top:0px;">
            <li>Shortage of trained and willing labor</li>
            <li>Minimum wage ($7.25 per hour in the US vs. 55 cents in Bangladesh)</li>
            <li>Difficulty in adopting automation in garment production </li>
          </ol>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Instead, the impact is expected to fall hardest on overseas factory workers. Dina Sidiqqi, an anthropologist at New York University, warned that manufacturers under pressure might cut wages or push employees to work longer hours just to stay afloat.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">The expenses for American consumers will rise, too. The Footwear Distributors and Retailers of America estimates that a $155 running shoe made in Vietnam could retail for $220 in US stores just to cover the 46% tariff. Economists fear that the supply chain chaos could hit pandemic levels.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 12px" />
