          <h2 style="              
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.5;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Ex-Meta employee makes an accusation</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5"><strong>Summary: Sarah Wynn-Williams testified in court, alleging Meta worked with China on censorship.</strong></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Former Meta executive Sarah Wynn-Williams accused the company of <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-04-2025-h3-4-putting-revenue-ahead-of-national-security" target="_blank">putting revenue ahead of national security</a>, claiming it built an $18B business in China by cooperating with the Chinese Communist Party. Speaking before the US Senate, she alleged Meta shared user data, including information on Americans, with Chinese authorities and developed censorship tools to meet Beijing’s demands.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">As an example, Wynn-Williams pointed to Meta’s decision to delete the Facebook account of Chinese dissident Guo Wengui, calling it evidence of Meta bowing to pressure from China. Meta denied the allegations, saying it does not operate its services in China, though it does generate ad revenue from Chinese companies. They also defended the decision to take down Guo's account for violating community standards.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Separately, Senator Josh Hawley accused Meta of threatening Wynn-Williams with a $50,000 penalty for testifying. They rejected that claim too, saying the penalty was tied to the breach of her 2017 separation agreement, not the testimony. </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Watch the Senate Committee Hearing <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-04-2025-h3-5-here" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

