                    "><strong>Prada has agreed to acquire Versace from Capri Holdings for $1.375B, including liabilities</strong>. Versace, recently losing its creative head, Donatella Versace, has been underperforming, while Prada remains strong. The acquisition follows multiple failed attempts to boost Prada’s brand portfolio with bold Versace aesthetics (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-11-04-2025-br3-8-press-release" target="_blank">press release</a>).</p>
